---
description: Deterministic document/report rendering conventions
globs: ["apps/docgen/**"]
alwaysApply: false
---

Reference: Technical Architecture 6.

- Every document (Annex 2/3/4, portfolio index, pre-primary assessment log,
  transition file, inspection pack) is a render of live rows at request
  time. Never persist a "generated document" as the source of truth — the
  DB rows are the source of truth; `document_render.source_row_hash` exists
  specifically to detect staleness of a cached render.
- Assessment log and transition file (pre-primary) are deterministic.
  Monthly/year-end narrative reports and the Annex 4 addendum are AI-drafted
  (Sonnet) then teacher-approved before release — same governance for both.
- Two hard environment requirements for this service specifically:
  1. `fonts-noto-core` must be in the base image — Devanagari text will not
     render correctly without it. Bake into the image, don't install ad hoc.
  2. The docx library swaps page width/height on landscape orientation. Any
     landscape template (e.g. a wide Annex 3 with many subject columns) must
     apply the corrective transform via the shared utility — don't re-solve
     this per template.
- Add a CI smoke test for both of the above (font rendering, landscape
  regression) — they're known failure modes, not hypothetical ones.
- The inspection pack is a batch invocation of the same per-document render
  functions, parameterized over a class/date range — do not build a separate
  compliance-export code path.
- Document access control mirrors the source data's RLS grain: a subject
  teacher cannot download another subject's Annex 3 sheet.
